The paper deals with privacy concerns in location-based systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a mechanism that involves testing the quality of predicted locations, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the category of data mining (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the mechanism, which falls under the category of performance evaluation (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with mobility traces, which is a topic that falls under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
